{
  "_comment": "MCP config template. Copy this file to .mcp.json (same directory) and add your own servers under mcpServers. Example entry: \"example-server\": { \"command\": \"npx\", \"args\": [\"-y\", \"@your-org/your-mcp-server\"], \"env\": { \"SERVER_URL\": \"https://your-server.example.com\" } }. For an HTTP/SSE server use: \"example-server\": { \"type\": \"sse\", \"url\": \"https://your-server.example.com/sse\" }. After adding a server, enable it in .claude/settings.json via enabledMcpjsonServers. Do NOT commit a real .mcp.json containing internal URLs or credentials.",
  "_disabled_examples_comment": "Common presets — not active. Move an entry into mcpServers to enable it, then allow-list it in .claude/settings.json under enabledMcpjsonServers.",
  "_disabled_examples": {
    "filesystem": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem", "<path>"]
    },
    "github": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-github"],
      "env": { "GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN": "<your-token>" }
    },
    "fetch": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-fetch"]
    }
  },
  "mcpServers": {}
}
